content:
Does anyone know why running mdbook serve in book/ keeps generating a file named src/coherence.md with the content:

# Content

?

I delete the file, and then git status shows:

On branch notation-docs
Your branch is up to date with 'origin/notation-docs'.

Changes not staged for commit:
  (use "git add <file>..." to update what will be committed)
  (use "git restore <file>..." to discard changes in working directory)
    modified:   book/book.toml

no changes added to commit (use "git add" and/or "git commit -a")

Then I go into /book and run mdbook build and lo and behold, git status shows:

On branch notation-docs
Your branch is up to date with 'origin/notation-docs'.

Changes not staged for commit:
  (use "git add <file>..." to update what will be committed)
  (use "git restore <file>..." to discard changes in working directory)
    modified:   book/book.toml

Untracked files:
  (use "git add <file>..." to include in what will be committed)
    book/src/coherence.md

no changes added to commit (use "git add" and/or "git commit -a")
Aha, someone forgot to remove it from the summary
Note to others: fixed; it was linking to the wrong page
